cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses a resource manager for distributed compute clouds, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper focuses on making it simple and transparent for researchers to deploy their scientific applications on cloud resources, which is relevant to this sub-category.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper may be relevant to this sub-category as it discusses the management of virtual machines in response to user job submissions, which may involve networking and internet architecture considerations.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may be relevant to this sub-category as it discusses the design and implementation of the Cloud Scheduler resource manager.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper may be relevant to this sub-category as it discusses the management of resources in distributed compute clouds, which may involve systems and control considerations.
